         <OBJECT_CONTRACT>
            <TITLE>
               <P>(NU/1346) Appointment of a financial Adviser to Provide Royalty Monetisation Advice and Services</P>
            </TITLE>
            <REFERENCE_NUMBER>NU/1346</REFERENCE_NUMBER>
            <CPV_MAIN>
               <CPV_CODE CODE="66171000"/>
            </CPV_MAIN>
            <TYPE_CONTRACT CTYPE="SERVICES"/>
            <SHORT_DESCR>
               <P>The University is aiming to monetize a revenue stream where a company will purchase all or a portion of a drug royalty in exchange for cash advances. In order to protect the University’s position and interest in this asset, specialist monetisation services are required to assist with monetisation process which will secure the best monetization deal.</P>
            </SHORT_DESCR>
            <NO_LOT_DIVISION/>
            <OBJECT_DESCR ITEM="1">
               <n2016:NUTS CODE="UKC22"/>
               <MAIN_SITE>
                  <P>The monetisation sale can be managed from any location worldwide.</P>
               </MAIN_SITE>
               <SHORT_DESCR>
                  <P>This procurement is for a single monetisation process from inception to closing the final deal.</P>
               </SHORT_DESCR>
               <AC_QUALITY>
                  <AC_CRITERION>Deal structures and programme</AC_CRITERION>
                  <AC_WEIGHTING>30</AC_WEIGHTING>
               </AC_QUALITY>
               <AC_QUALITY>
                  <AC_CRITERION>Knowledge of royalty purchasers</AC_CRITERION>
                  <AC_WEIGHTING>15</AC_WEIGHTING>
               </AC_QUALITY>
               <AC_QUALITY>
                  <AC_CRITERION>Proposed team for this monetisation</AC_CRITERION>
                  <AC_WEIGHTING>15</AC_WEIGHTING>
               </AC_QUALITY>
               <AC_COST>
                  <AC_CRITERION>Fees</AC_CRITERION>
                  <AC_WEIGHTING>40</AC_WEIGHTING>
               </AC_COST>
               <NO_OPTIONS/>
               <NO_EU_PROGR_RELATED/>
            </OBJECT_DESCR>
         </OBJECT_CONTRACT>
